TestOutputAskDownstreamVariableAnnotatesAsAsk
/ output.ask write-target annotates as (ask) downstream — its reflected
/ return type is Data<Ask>. Ask.ToString() returns the Answer string so
/ downstream code can still interpolate %answer% as text, but the type
/ identity in the snapshot stays "ask". (Test-designer's original spec
/ said "string"; reconfirmed with Ingi 2026-05-27 — match reflected type
/ for consistency with every other action.)
- builder.goals from 'probes/ask/', write to %goals%
- goal.getTypes %goals[0]%, write to %snapshot%
- set %annot% = %snapshot[1].answer%
- assert.equals expected='ask', actual=%annot%
